==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fictitious
<hw>Fic*ti"tious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fictitius</ets>. See <er>Fiction</er>.]</ety> <def>Feigned;
imaginary; not real; fabulous; counterfeit; false; not genuine; <as>as,
<ex>fictitious</ex> fame</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The human persons are as <qex>fictitious</qex> as the airy
ones.</q> <rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Fic*ti"tious*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Fic*ti"tious*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fictive</ent>⟦br⟧
